com.cs371group2.concern

Enum ConcernStatus

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ConcernStatus>
      • com.cs371group2.concern.ConcernStatus
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<ConcernStatus>

    public enum ConcernStatus
extends Enum<ConcernStatus>
    The concern status enum is used to determine the state of the concern within the system. When concerns are first received they have a pending status. This status will then be changed to send, responding, and resolved as the concern is acted up. Created on 2017-01-17.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      PENDING
      When a concern is first received its status is set to pending.
      RESOLVED
      When a concern has been responded to its status will be changed to resolved meaning the concern has been addressed.
      RESPONDING24
      When a concern has been seen and will be acted upon within the next 24 hours its status will be changed to this.
      RESPONDING48
      When a concern has been seen and will be acted upon within the next 48 hours its status will be changed to this.
      RESPONDING72
      When a concern has been seen and will be acted upon within the next 72 hours its status will be changed to this.
      RETRACTED
      If a reporter decides to retract their concern then the status will be changed to retracted.
      SEEN
      When a concern has been received and opened by an administrator its status will be changed to seen.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • PENDING

        public static final ConcernStatus PENDING
        When a concern is first received its status is set to pending. This means that the concern has been submitted but has not been acknowledged by an administrator yet.

      • SEEN

        public static final ConcernStatus SEEN
        When a concern has been received and opened by an administrator its status will be changed to seen.

      • RESPONDING24

        public static final ConcernStatus RESPONDING24
        When a concern has been seen and will be acted upon within the next 24 hours its status will be changed to this.

      • RESPONDING48

        public static final ConcernStatus RESPONDING48
        When a concern has been seen and will be acted upon within the next 48 hours its status will be changed to this. 48 hours is based on the priority of the concern. This does NOT mean that the status will change again to responding 24. It only means that the concern will be responded to sometime in the next 48 hours.

      • RESPONDING72

        public static final ConcernStatus RESPONDING72
        When a concern has been seen and will be acted upon within the next 72 hours its status will be changed to this. 72 hours is based on the priority of the concern. This does NOT mean that the status will change again to responding 24 or 48. It only means that the concern will be responded to sometime in the next 72 hours.

      • RESOLVED

        public static final ConcernStatus RESOLVED
        When a concern has been responded to its status will be changed to resolved meaning the concern has been addressed.

      • RETRACTED

        public static final ConcernStatus RETRACTED
        If a reporter decides to retract their concern then the status will be changed to retracted. Retracting a concern is only allowed if the status is pending or seen.
